	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Quick replies can be annoying, so I'm not sure that encouraging such a practice would be a good idea.
<br />
<br />I mean, how often in a rich/meaningful discussion are quick comments (without quotes to previous posts) called for? I don't think too often, and I'd rather keep the discussions meaningful than risk making them empty quick comments fests just because some people think that clicking the "post reply" button is too much trouble.
<br />
<br />I'm not saying anything against you Nathan, you probably miss this feature because you use it in some other forum, so I understand why you want it. But IMO, NESDEV has a lot of members that focus on actual content, differently from most forums out there, which have a lot of "noise". My concern is that enabling quick replies might increase the level of noise.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


